## Constraints (invariants)

λ constraints() = {
  // execution ordering
  top-down-order: S5 ⟶ S4 ⟶ S3 ⟶ S2 ⟶ S1  // S5 must be solid before S4

  // observation before proposal
  observe-before-propose: scan(root/specs/)  // recursively, before asking questions

  // every lambda needs grounding
  every-lambda-has-prose: λ(...) → must include plain-English explanation

  // completeness check
  surface-missing: for each principle(λ), ask → what companion should exist alongside it?

  // human gate
  human-approve: present complete file → read each λ with prose → confirm → then write
  // no-write-without-approval: architecture.md written only after explicit confirm

  // preamble dedup
  no-duplicate-preamble: nucleus preamble loaded via .clinerules/00-gybis.md
  // invariant: preamble appears exactly once, first
}

